    &lt;h1&gt;Up and running on Jekyll&lt;/h1&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;meta&quot;&gt;March 15, 2016&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;p class=&quot;drop-cap-p&quot;&gt;Yes this site is not run in WordPress; yes it is statically generated by Jekyll. What is Jekyll? There are only a few reasons I have used Jekyll.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;Speed&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;Modularity&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;Free hosting&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;For the most part, I previously used WordPress because of how modular it was to create a style/theme. It ensured that I didn&#39;t duplicate common things like the header and footer. Simple stuff.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;The free hosting is from Github allowing me to any front end code I choose. The only drawback is I cannot have anything that is server side like a contact form.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;I&#39;ve decided not to use a contact form as it&#39;s pretty useless for my uses. If someone really wants to contact me, they can click my email on the left if you&#39;re on desktop and in the footer if you&#39;re on mobile.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;That&#39;s it, thanks for visiting!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

